1
00:00:10,767 --> 00:00:12,233
<i> Wait a minute, what is that?</i>

2
00:00:12,367 --> 00:00:13,300
<i> This is for my friend.</i>

3
00:00:13,433 --> 00:00:15,067
<i>I don't believe you!
Give that to me!</i>

4
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:17,267
<i> Let it go, Astrid.</i>

5
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:18,067
<i> Emma!</i>

6
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:20,667
<i> I love Mommy Emma and not you.</i>

7
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:22,700
<i>- Mookie!
- Shut up!</i>

8
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:24,867
<i> Mommy Emma!</i>

9
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:26,433
<i> Mookie, sweetie.</i>

10
00:00:26,567 --> 00:00:27,967
<i> Mommy's here!</i>

11
00:00:28,100 --> 00:00:30,767
<i>Hello, Mom. We need your help
to find Mookie.</i>

12
00:00:34,700 --> 00:00:36,033
<i> Let me go!</i>

13
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:39,367
<i>I won't let you take
my daughter away from me!</i>

14
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:41,333
<i> Don't ever hurt Emma.</i>

15
00:00:41,467 --> 00:00:43,067
<i> You two shouldn't be fighting.</i>

16
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:44,467
<i> She's your sibling.</i>

17
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:48,600
<i>Our family lawyer gave us this
picture when Mom and Dad died.</i>

18
00:00:48,733 --> 00:00:51,100
<i> Ligaya wrote this letter.</i>

19
00:00:51,233 --> 00:00:54,000
<i> No! No!</i>

20
00:01:31,967 --> 00:01:33,067
Olive, sweetie.

21
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:37,767
I know that it's hard
to believe.

22
00:01:38,833 --> 00:01:46,900
But I've been praying to God
to help me find you.

23
00:01:47,067 --> 00:01:48,067
Mom.

24
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:49,800
Mom, is it true?

25
00:01:49,933 --> 00:01:51,833
Is she really your sister?

26
00:01:53,233 --> 00:01:56,867
God answered my prayers.

27
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:00,100
That's why we met.

28
00:02:00,233 --> 00:02:03,000
We're all together now.

29
00:02:03,133 --> 00:02:06,900
I need you to understand,
you have to believe me.

30
00:02:07,033 --> 00:02:12,167
You're just saying that
to keep me from hurting Emma.

31
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:13,133
That's not true.

32
00:02:13,267 --> 00:02:14,400
You're just trying
to save her from me!

33
00:02:14,567 --> 00:02:17,200
No, that's not true.
You have to believe me.

34
00:02:17,333 --> 00:02:20,467
And even if you're telling
the truth.

35
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:23,467
I'm still not gonna let you have
my daughter!

36
00:02:24,900 --> 00:02:26,300
Especially you!

37
00:02:27,933 --> 00:02:31,733
I can never accept you
as my sister!

38
00:02:31,867 --> 00:02:33,333
I feel the same way!

39
00:02:33,933 --> 00:02:35,867
Of all the cruel things you've
done to me and my daughter,

40
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,900
I will never forgive you!

41
00:02:44,633 --> 00:02:46,533
Olive, let's talk.
Please, let's talk.

42
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:48,433
I can't let this happen!

43
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:50,267
No!

44
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:54,100
You're just saying that
to fool me!

45
00:02:54,233 --> 00:02:55,667
You're lying!

46
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,600
It's not true!

47
00:02:57,933 --> 00:03:01,033
- Sweetie! Come on!
- Please, stop!

48
00:03:01,167 --> 00:03:03,100
Go ahead! We won't force you
to believe us.

49
00:03:03,233 --> 00:03:04,900
But don't disrespect my mom!

50
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:07,333
Police!

51
00:03:09,067 --> 00:03:10,233
You have to surrender.

52
00:03:10,367 --> 00:03:10,867
Never!

53
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:13,433
I can't go to prison!

54
00:03:13,567 --> 00:03:18,267
- Get out of my way! Move!
- Olive!

55
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:20,067
Mommy!

56
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:22,167
Olive, sweetie!

57
00:03:22,333 --> 00:03:23,133
I'm gonna follow her.

58
00:03:23,267 --> 00:03:24,400
- Mom, no.
- Stay here, I've got her.

59
00:03:24,533 --> 00:03:25,400
Olive!

60
00:03:25,533 --> 00:03:26,833
Come here, Mom.

61
00:03:32,267 --> 00:03:33,033
Mom.

62
00:03:33,167 --> 00:03:34,333
Are you hurt?

63
00:03:59,900 --> 00:04:04,533
Thank God you guys are safe.

64
00:04:06,667 --> 00:04:10,500
Sweetie, are you sure you're
okay?

65
00:04:11,833 --> 00:04:13,900
Yes, I'm okay.

66
00:04:15,133 --> 00:04:17,900
How can I not be safe
when I have you guys?

67
00:04:18,033 --> 00:04:20,900
Mom, Dad, Grandmother.

68
00:04:24,767 --> 00:04:27,600
I'm glad to have you back safe
and sound.

69
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:47,133
Sir, where are he other
officers?

70
00:04:47,267 --> 00:04:50,033
Olive got away.

71
00:04:50,167 --> 00:04:51,300
Jade chased after her.

72
00:04:51,433 --> 00:04:54,267
I already called them,
don't worry.

73
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:55,333
Thank you.

74
00:05:04,967 --> 00:05:05,967
Miss Caparas!

75
00:05:07,467 --> 00:05:08,367
Miss Caparas!

76
00:05:10,233 --> 00:05:12,900
Miss Caparas! Surrender now!

77
00:05:15,933 --> 00:05:17,067
Miss Caparas!

78
00:06:22,133 --> 00:06:23,467
No, no.

79
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:24,467
Be quiet!

80
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:28,033
Olive. I'm so sorry,
but I'm not like you.

81
00:06:28,167 --> 00:06:31,900
You let me deal with addiction
on my own before.

82
00:06:32,033 --> 00:06:35,700
I'm sorry, but I can't let you
become a horrible person.

83
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:37,600
No!

84
00:06:37,733 --> 00:06:38,833
No, Jade, please!

85
00:06:38,967 --> 00:06:40,333
No!

86
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:42,433
Officers!

87
00:06:42,567 --> 00:06:44,267
She's over here!

88
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:47,133
- No! No! Jade.
- Come get her! Officers!

89
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:50,233
Olive, please.
You have to surrender.

90
00:06:50,867 --> 00:06:52,633
Just cooperate with them.

91
00:06:52,767 --> 00:06:54,333
I can't do that!

92
00:06:54,467 --> 00:06:55,000
No!

93
00:06:56,433 --> 00:06:58,533
How could you betray your own
sister?

94
00:06:58,667 --> 00:06:59,767
I'm sorry, Olive.

95
00:07:01,067 --> 00:07:03,100
But I can't let you get
away with this,

96
00:07:03,233 --> 00:07:05,500
I can't condone your bad
behaviour.

97
00:07:07,167 --> 00:07:11,800
Olive, I'm doing this
for your own good.

98
00:07:11,933 --> 00:07:13,633
You're going to regret this!

99
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,500
You're going to regret this,
Jade!

100
00:07:15,633 --> 00:07:18,567
I just want you
to have a second chance,

101
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:19,867
because I love you.

102
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,033
No!

103
00:07:21,167 --> 00:07:22,767
You don't love me!

104
00:07:24,067 --> 00:07:24,800
Olive.

105
00:07:26,167 --> 00:07:28,267
I'm so sorry, Olive.

106
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:29,767
Sorry?

107
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:32,267
After everything I did
to take care of you

108
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:33,767
while you were dealing
with your addiction!

109
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:35,900
This is how you're going
to repay me?

110
00:07:36,033 --> 00:07:36,800
No!

111
00:07:36,933 --> 00:07:38,433
Just cooperate with them.

112
00:07:38,567 --> 00:07:41,400
We can convince Emma
to forgive you.

113
00:07:41,533 --> 00:07:45,567
Ligaya will help us.
Emma is a good person.

114
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:48,200
I don't need their forgiveness.

115
00:07:48,367 --> 00:07:51,333
All I ever want is to be with
Mookie!

116
00:07:51,467 --> 00:07:54,800
The child I raised!

117
00:07:54,933 --> 00:07:57,600
Why can't you understand?

118
00:07:57,733 --> 00:07:59,933
You've never been a mother!

119
00:08:00,067 --> 00:08:02,100
That's why you can't understand
me!

120
00:08:03,133 --> 00:08:03,900
Olive.

121
00:08:04,033 --> 00:08:05,200
Olive, I will help you.

122
00:08:05,333 --> 00:08:07,900
Ligaya's here for us.
Emma and Mookie, too.

123
00:08:08,033 --> 00:08:09,933
We have a family now.

124
00:08:10,067 --> 00:08:12,267
I don't need them!

125
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:15,867
And I can never accept them
as my family!

126
00:08:17,967 --> 00:08:19,767
You will pay for this, Jade.

127
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:21,833
- Miss Caparas.
- You'll see!

128
00:08:23,733 --> 00:08:27,300
The officers need our statement,
so we should go to the precinct.

129
00:08:27,433 --> 00:08:28,967
Wait, I'll come with you.

130
00:08:29,100 --> 00:08:31,033
Olive might try to hurt you.

131
00:08:31,167 --> 00:08:32,733
Danilo, what are you saying?

132
00:08:32,867 --> 00:08:33,867
She'll be at the police station,

133
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,967
and she'll be surrounded
by police officers.

134
00:08:36,100 --> 00:08:38,033
And we'll be with them.

135
00:08:38,167 --> 00:08:39,533
That's right.

136
00:08:39,667 --> 00:08:44,567
You should go see the doctor.
To tend to your wounds.

137
00:08:44,700 --> 00:08:46,400
We'll take care of him.

138
00:08:46,533 --> 00:08:48,767
Yes, we'll make sure he's safe.

139
00:08:48,900 --> 00:08:51,467
I'll drive him to the hospital.

140
00:08:55,167 --> 00:08:56,567
Thank you, Zayn.

141
00:09:00,333 --> 00:09:03,167
We'll see you once we're done
at the precinct.

142
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:05,600
Thank you.

143
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,133
Take care, okay.

144
00:09:08,267 --> 00:09:08,833
Okay, Emma.

145
00:09:08,967 --> 00:09:10,733
- Careful.
- Take care.

146
00:09:10,867 --> 00:09:12,100
Be safe, Dad.

147
00:09:13,533 --> 00:09:15,867
Mom, we'll meet you there.

148
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,733
This way, ma'am.

149
00:09:17,867 --> 00:09:19,333
I'll go this way.

150
00:09:19,467 --> 00:09:20,233
Okay.

151
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:40,233
I'm just going to finalize your
statement.

152
00:09:40,367 --> 00:09:43,300
The car transporting
Miss Caparas broke down.

153
00:09:43,433 --> 00:09:45,233
But they'll be here soon.

154
00:09:45,367 --> 00:09:48,067
Thank God, Olive got caught.

155
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,133
Excuse me.

156
00:09:51,333 --> 00:09:54,200
Sweetie, how are you doing?

157
00:09:55,133 --> 00:09:56,900
I'm okay, Mom.

158
00:09:57,033 --> 00:09:58,633
How are you?

159
00:09:58,767 --> 00:10:00,300
I'm okay now.

160
00:10:00,433 --> 00:10:03,333
I'm glad your wound has been
tended to.

161
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:06,500
I'm sorry that I have
to bring you here.

162
00:10:06,633 --> 00:10:08,200
Don't worry,
after they get our statement,

163
00:10:08,333 --> 00:10:10,667
we're gonna go see your dad
at the hospital.

164
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:11,900
I also want them
to check on you.

165
00:10:12,033 --> 00:10:13,933
I don't know what other
medicines...

166
00:10:14,067 --> 00:10:17,767
Mom, don't worry about me.

167
00:10:17,900 --> 00:10:20,867
You've done a lot
to protect me.

168
00:10:22,233 --> 00:10:23,633
You got hurt too.

169
00:10:24,867 --> 00:10:28,233
Sweetie, I will do anything
for you.

170
00:10:28,367 --> 00:10:30,600
I don't want to see you
getting hurt.

171
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:33,567
Olive has no mercy.

172
00:10:35,933 --> 00:10:40,633
Mom, Grandmother, I'm sorry
about Mommy's behaviour.

173
00:10:40,767 --> 00:10:43,367
Sweetie, it's not your fault.

174
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:45,333
You don't need to apologize.

175
00:10:47,433 --> 00:10:49,533
She's right, Mookie.

176
00:10:50,567 --> 00:10:53,200
You've done nothing wrong.

177
00:10:53,333 --> 00:10:56,133
She might change her ways.

178
00:10:56,267 --> 00:10:59,433
Now that she knows
that you're her mom.

179
00:10:59,567 --> 00:11:01,267
And you're her sister.

180
00:11:03,967 --> 00:11:07,900
Will you ever forgive her
if she apologizes

181
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:12,067
and says she'll change?

182
00:11:17,233 --> 00:11:20,867
Since I have many shortcomings
towards her,

183
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,833
I can forgive her easily.

184
00:11:26,233 --> 00:11:31,667
Let me go! I said, Let me go!
You can't detain me!

185
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:34,900
I need to talk to my lawyer!
Let me go!

186
00:11:36,867 --> 00:11:41,500
You can never get away
from all that you've done!

187
00:11:42,567 --> 00:11:43,933
I have a lot of money!

188
00:11:44,933 --> 00:11:47,167
I can do anything I want!

189
00:11:47,300 --> 00:11:51,633
Just wait and see!

190
00:11:56,733 --> 00:11:57,767
My daughter.

191
00:11:57,900 --> 00:11:59,367
Don't ever call me that!

192
00:12:01,733 --> 00:12:03,733
We're not related!

193
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:07,567
Sweetie,

194
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:10,467
your punishment will be lessened
if you confess to your crime.

195
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:15,167
I won't confess to anything!
I didn't do anything wrong.

196
00:12:15,333 --> 00:12:17,267
I'm innocent!

197
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:18,367
- I'm innocent!
- Miss Caparas.

198
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:20,167
- I didn't do anything wrong!
- Miss Caparas.

199
00:12:20,300 --> 00:12:21,533
Miss Caparas.

200
00:12:21,667 --> 00:12:23,667
They have solid evidence
against you.

201
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:25,967
Your lawyer will advise you
on what to do.

202
00:12:26,100 --> 00:12:27,667
Once they file the case
against you,

203
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:29,267
we'll transfer you
to the city jail.

204
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:31,533
But we'll have to detain you
here for now.

205
00:12:31,667 --> 00:12:32,500
No!

206
00:12:32,633 --> 00:12:33,567
No, Mookie!

207
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:35,933
- Mookie, Mookie!
- Come on.

208
00:12:36,067 --> 00:12:39,733
Mookie!
Tell them I'm your mom.

209
00:12:39,867 --> 00:12:42,500
Mookie! Mookie!

210
00:12:43,900 --> 00:12:45,533
Let me go!

211
00:12:56,333 --> 00:12:58,067
The doctor checked on me.

212
00:12:58,333 --> 00:12:59,900
They did tests on me, too.

213
00:13:00,033 --> 00:13:04,633
Olive is so rotten!
I'm glad the police got her now.

214
00:13:04,767 --> 00:13:06,833
What a revelation.

215
00:13:06,967 --> 00:13:08,800
It's a prime event!

216
00:13:08,933 --> 00:13:11,233
I'm glad you're safe now.

217
00:13:11,367 --> 00:13:12,733
Right.

218
00:13:12,867 --> 00:13:14,133
But wait,

219
00:13:14,267 --> 00:13:23,367
is it true that Olive and Jade
are Ligaya's twins?

220
00:13:23,533 --> 00:13:24,800
Is that true, Danilo?

221
00:13:25,933 --> 00:13:31,400
So, if Olive is Ligaya's
daughter,

222
00:13:31,533 --> 00:13:35,500
that only means she's Emma's
sister.

223
00:13:36,967 --> 00:13:38,133
That's insane!

224
00:13:38,267 --> 00:13:40,167
I can't believe it!

225
00:13:40,300 --> 00:13:41,633
- I know, right?
- Right.

226
00:13:41,767 --> 00:13:43,800
I can't believe it myself
either.

227
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:48,200
But everything that Jade said
and the pictures she has prove

228
00:13:49,767 --> 00:13:51,600
that they're Ligaya's twin.

229
00:13:53,267 --> 00:13:55,300
They're Emma's sisters.

230
00:13:55,467 --> 00:13:57,767
So what's gonna happen now?

231
00:13:57,900 --> 00:14:03,200
Will Emma let Olive get away
with everything she's done?

232
00:14:03,333 --> 00:14:04,667
Is that it?

233
00:14:04,800 --> 00:14:06,267
No, no.

234
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:08,333
The way Emma feels towards
Olive,

235
00:14:10,100 --> 00:14:11,933
she won't be able
to forgive her.

236
00:14:20,467 --> 00:14:21,633
Miss Caparas.

237
00:14:21,767 --> 00:14:23,000
- Please just cooperate with us.
- Please don't detain me here.

238
00:14:23,133 --> 00:14:23,933
No, I won't let you do this.

239
00:14:24,067 --> 00:14:26,267
Miss Caparas, just cooperate
with us.

240
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:27,533
I didn't do anything wrong.

241
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:29,033
- Don't put me in jail.
- Miss Caparas.

242
00:14:29,167 --> 00:14:29,567
Please, don't detain me!

243
00:14:29,700 --> 00:14:31,433
I'm begging you.

244
00:14:31,567 --> 00:14:33,233
Please, don't detain me here.

245
00:14:33,367 --> 00:14:34,667
I will do anything you want!

246
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:37,900
Sir, how much do you want?
Aren't you greedy for money?

247
00:14:38,033 --> 00:14:39,367
You want money, right?

248
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:41,133
Come on, please.
Don't detain me here!

249
00:14:41,267 --> 00:14:43,100
Get me out of here!

250
00:14:43,233 --> 00:14:45,133
Get me out!

251
00:14:45,267 --> 00:14:48,667
Sir, please!
You have a family, right?

252
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:51,200
I have a family too.
I have Mookie.

253
00:14:51,333 --> 00:14:53,433
Mookie is my daughter.
She needs me.

254
00:14:53,567 --> 00:14:56,967
I'm begging you, please.
Get me out of here!

255
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:58,800
Get me out of here!

256
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:04,900
Please, please,
get me out of here.

257
00:15:05,033 --> 00:15:08,233
Get me out of here!
I'm innocent!

258
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:15,233
What are you looking at?

259
00:15:23,233 --> 00:15:26,367
Get me out of here, please.

260
00:15:35,367 --> 00:15:37,033
How are you feeling?

261
00:15:38,633 --> 00:15:41,033
Didn't you hear what
the doctor said?

262
00:15:42,167 --> 00:15:43,567
He said I can go home now.

263
00:15:45,133 --> 00:15:45,967
How about you?

264
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:48,233
Are you okay?

265
00:15:49,633 --> 00:15:51,133
Don't worry about me.

266
00:15:53,533 --> 00:15:55,000
What about you, Mookie?

267
00:15:56,733 --> 00:15:57,800
How are you?

268
00:15:58,900 --> 00:15:59,967
I'm okay.

269
00:16:01,567 --> 00:16:04,067
I'm just sad about our
situation,

270
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:07,700
you're fighting with each other,

271
00:16:10,133 --> 00:16:12,567
and it turned out that mommy
is your sister.

272
00:16:16,733 --> 00:16:18,367
Don't worry about that.

273
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:21,700
Even though Olive
and I are related,

274
00:16:23,333 --> 00:16:25,833
she still committed a crime
against you.

275
00:16:25,967 --> 00:16:28,067
And she has to pay for it.

276
00:16:35,933 --> 00:16:37,067
Thanks again.

277
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:39,367
No worries, it's nothing.

278
00:16:40,467 --> 00:16:46,433
I wish I had helped you out when
you were suffering before.

279
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:48,933
Anyway, how are you doing now?

280
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:51,433
I'm okay.

281
00:16:54,033 --> 00:16:58,400
I still can't forget what Olive
did to me.

282
00:17:01,033 --> 00:17:03,033
And I'm worried
about Mommy Emma.

283
00:17:03,167 --> 00:17:07,100
She just found out
that Olive is her sister.

284
00:17:09,267 --> 00:17:12,733
I hope Olive will get better.

285
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:15,867
You're so kind.

286
00:17:16,967 --> 00:17:21,900
Even though your mom harmed you,
you still wish her well.

287
00:17:24,767 --> 00:17:26,900
You know what,
I used to think that...

288
00:17:30,667 --> 00:17:33,900
I didn't have a family.

289
00:17:36,567 --> 00:17:38,900
But I realized that...

290
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:45,067
I am loved by many.

291
00:17:46,233 --> 00:17:49,300
That's true, cause I love you..

292
00:17:51,467 --> 00:17:52,567
What?

293
00:17:52,700 --> 00:17:53,767
As a friend.

294
00:17:53,900 --> 00:17:55,533
As a friend, of course.

295
00:17:56,800 --> 00:17:57,767
Right?

296
00:18:03,033 --> 00:18:04,967
Zayn, thanks again.

297
00:18:07,133 --> 00:18:12,633
I'm so lucky to have you guys.

298
00:18:14,533 --> 00:18:18,467
I just wish that Mommy
would get better soon.

299
00:18:19,933 --> 00:18:23,633
I wish her well, so we can all
live in peace.

300
00:18:55,533 --> 00:18:56,633
<i> What?</i>

301
00:18:56,767 --> 00:18:58,167
<i> Are you happy now?</i>

302
00:18:58,300 --> 00:19:02,700
<i>You don't know how painful it is
to see you like this, Olive.</i>

303
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:07,733
<i> If you only knew how I feel.</i>

304
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:15,500
<i>I just want what's best for you.</i>

305
00:19:17,867 --> 00:19:19,700
<i> If that's what you want...</i>

306
00:19:19,833 --> 00:19:21,533
<i> Then help me, Jade.</i>

307
00:19:23,267 --> 00:19:24,867
<i> Get me out of here.</i>

308
00:19:26,633 --> 00:19:30,133
<i>I don't want to stay in this
stinky, crowded place.</i>

309
00:19:30,300 --> 00:19:35,033
<i>Jade, help me. I'm gonna lose
my mind here, please.</i>

310
00:19:35,167 --> 00:19:36,867
<i> I know, Olive.</i>

311
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:38,967
<i> Then do something!</i>

312
00:19:39,100 --> 00:19:40,767
<i> Get me out of here!</i>

313
00:19:42,133 --> 00:19:46,600
<i>Talk to them, tell them
that I'm innocent.</i>

314
00:19:46,733 --> 00:19:51,100
<i>Tell them Emma's lying
just to get Mookie away from me.</i>

315
00:19:51,233 --> 00:19:52,633
<i> Jade, please.</i>

316
00:19:52,767 --> 00:19:54,567
<i> Please, help me.</i>

317
00:19:54,700 --> 00:19:58,967
<i>Olive, we have to do what's
right.</i>

318
00:20:00,667 --> 00:20:03,567
<i>I'm sure you won't be staying
here for long.</i>

319
00:20:06,633 --> 00:20:08,633
<i> The moment you get released,</i>

320
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:11,667
<i> we'll get you medical help.</i>

321
00:20:16,167 --> 00:20:17,700
<i> Get out of my sight!</i>

322
00:20:17,833 --> 00:20:18,933
<i> But Olive.</i>

323
00:20:19,067 --> 00:20:20,433
<i> Get out of my sight!</i>

324
00:20:21,533 --> 00:20:22,800
<i> Leave!</i>

325
00:20:48,433 --> 00:20:49,900
Mookie, where's Mookie?

326
00:20:50,033 --> 00:20:52,533
Mookie's with Wiro.

327
00:20:53,733 --> 00:20:56,433
The psychiatrist checked on her.

328
00:20:56,567 --> 00:20:58,900
We have a brave daughter.

329
00:20:59,033 --> 00:21:01,067
She tried so hard
to be strong

330
00:21:01,200 --> 00:21:04,267
after everything she's been
through with Olive.

331
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:07,067
I hope she won't get
traumatized by it.

332
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:11,900
I hope she's doing well.

333
00:21:16,767 --> 00:21:18,600
And you, Emma.

334
00:21:18,733 --> 00:21:21,767
I know that finding out
that Olive is your sister

335
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:23,167
affects you tremendously.

336
00:21:27,833 --> 00:21:29,767
Don't worry, Dan.

337
00:21:29,900 --> 00:21:36,900
Nothing will change my decision
against her.

338
00:21:37,033 --> 00:21:39,300
She took Mookie away from us.

339
00:21:39,433 --> 00:21:41,333
She tortured her.

340
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:44,900
I have no mercy for her.

341
00:21:47,267 --> 00:21:49,000
I understand how you feel, Emma.

342
00:21:50,167 --> 00:21:52,700
But I'm worried about my mom.

343
00:21:52,833 --> 00:21:55,333
I know she'll take this hard.

344
00:21:58,567 --> 00:22:02,133
I can't blame her for having
maternal feelings for Olive.

345
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:06,167
But I wish she would consider
my feelings, too.

346
00:22:52,467 --> 00:22:53,500
Olive, sweetie.

347
00:22:57,067 --> 00:22:59,267
Don't lose hope, okay?

348
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:04,367
Mommy's here now.

349
00:23:04,500 --> 00:23:08,167
I will do everything
to help you.

350
00:23:20,667 --> 00:23:23,400
Please drop the charges against
your sister.

351
00:23:23,567 --> 00:23:25,700
Please, do it for me.

352
00:23:25,833 --> 00:23:29,000
No! I have money!
I can pay for everything!

353
00:23:29,133 --> 00:23:31,467
I know how dubious you are!

354
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:35,200
You're using our mom to get away
from your crime.

355
00:23:35,333 --> 00:23:37,067
You can rot in this jail!

356
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:39,600
Did Emma tell you
that she's going to see Olive?

357
00:23:39,733 --> 00:23:40,600
Yes, she did.

358
00:23:40,733 --> 00:23:42,467
You shouldn't have let her go.

359
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:44,900
She probably just wants
to talk to Olive.

360
00:23:45,033 --> 00:23:46,567
We never know, they might
make amends with each other.

361
00:23:46,700 --> 00:23:49,533
We've thought of a defense
to get you out of prison.

362
00:23:49,667 --> 00:23:50,733
What is it?

363
00:23:50,867 --> 00:23:53,633
I can't leave without Mookie.

364
00:23:55,767 --> 00:23:58,033
- Olive!
- Go on!

365
00:23:58,167 --> 00:23:59,633
Don't even try it!

366
00:23:59,767 --> 00:24:01,267
I will shoot her head off!

367
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:02,300
Olive!
